<recipe>
<title>
Eggplant and Tomato Pasta
</title>
<details>

</details>
<ingredients>
1 (16 oz.) box dried, shaped pasta (I used rigatoni)
1 medium eggplant
1 c . chopped onion
5 cloves garlic , minced
2 (15 oz.) cans tomato sauce
1 tsp . granulated sugar
1 tsp . dried sweet basil
1/2 tsp . dried oregano
1/4 c . grated Romano cheese
4 oz . fresh mozzarella , in small cubes
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Cook pasta according to package directions.
Peel eggplant, and slice it into 1/4-inch round slices.
Sprinkle top with salt; let it sit for 15 minutes.
Flip eggplant slices over, and sprinkle with salt. Let it sit for 15 more minutes.
Rinse eggplant, and pat dry.
Cut eggplant into 1/2-inch pieces; set aside.
In a large skillet over medium-low heat, heat olive oil.
Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until soft.
Stir in garlic and cook for 1 more minute.
Add the eggplant, tomato sauce, sugar, basil, and oregano.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until the eggplant is tender, about 10-15 minutes.
Stir in Romano cheese.
Add the cooked pasta and fresh mozzarella to sauce, and toss to coat.
Serve pasta topped with extra Romano cheese and fresh basil, if desired.
</instructions>
</recipe>
